⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Katerina Ivanovna
node CRP · CRP · ⟦Katerina Ivanovna:CRP:77dbcb⟧

WHO   — Katerina Ivanovna — the consumptive widow · pride and madness
WHAT  — The tragedy of wounded pride: dying of consumption, she parades her ‘noble’ origins, breaks down at the funeral dinner, and dies raving in the street.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel shows poverty's assault on dignity — pride with nowhere to stand becomes a kind of madness.
HOW   — By tuberculosis, humiliation, and a fevered insistence on a respectability the world has stripped from her.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I came of a good family — I will not be pitied like a beggar — and I died in the gutter still insisting on it.

